# 8. 最後まで

Student A: “Hey, wanna try doing some acting with me?”
Student B: “Huh? Why are you asking me...?”
Student A: “Because our fates were sealed the second we were born into nobility. We don't have a choice.”
Student A: “But I don't plan on being tied down like this forever. Doesn't it just bore you out of your mind?”
Student B: “I mean...”
Student A: “We can be whatever we want on stage! And I know you'd love it.”
Audience: Huh... Are those boys on stage students?
Audience: Probably. I've never seen them before...
Audience: Me neither...
Audience: They really have me on the edge of my seat.
Emu: ...!
Teacher: “Hey, don't you all know that it's past curfew?!”
Student A: “Whoa, busted! Guys, run!!”
Student B: “This is why I said that we shouldn't hold practice so late at night!”
Teacher: “Stop right this second!”
Audience: Oh, I didn't realize that actor could play such a comical character...
Audience: Hehe. Me neither. This is a little different from what we're used to, but I kinda like it.
Student B: “This is it. Our very first showing.”
Student A: “Yeah. We managed to make it this far.”
Student B: “I have to think that even you're feeling nervous right now.”
Student A: “No way! If anything, I've never been more excited.”
Student A: “I mean, we're about to go out there and put on an unforgettable performance for everyone.”
Emu: (Okay, that's the end...)
Emu: (How's the crowd going to...?)
Emu: ...!
Byakkomachi: Wow. They're getting a standing ovation...
Emu: Y-Yeah...!
Announcement: <That concludes this showing. Please be sure not to forget any of your belongings.>
Tsukasa: That was a spectacular performance...! So this is the new show format Kikyogumi will be trying!
Rui: At a school for the children of nobles, a group of outcasts forms a troupe.
Rui: The protagonist was thought to have the worst acting skills in the troupe, but he hid the fact that he was the prince of the neighboring land... I particularly liked that bit.
Tsukasa: Yes! And I was moved by each cast member's powerful acting performance.
Nene: Me too... The veterans were obviously really good...
Nene: But the students really held their own.
Rui: Indeed. Of course, they were a little rough around the edges...
Rui: But that ended up being just one more reason for the audience to cheer them on.
Tsukasa: Very true! I learned a lot by watching them!
Nene: ...
Rui: Nene?
Nene: Uhh...
Nene: So, I was hoping to tell Emu and Byakkomachi my thoughts on the show...
Tsukasa: Ah, yes! They were sitting in the section for invited guests, but where could they be...?
Emu's Voice: You guys!
Byakkomachi: Hello. It's been a little while.
Emu: What did you think of the new Kikyogumi?!
Tsukasa: It was absolutely astonishing!!
Tsukasa: The show we saw before involved pulling the audience into the world of the story by way of masterful acting, precision action and extraordinary singing...
Tsukasa: But the show we just saw involved a different kind of energy.
Rui: I agree. While the veterans used their talents to skillfully set up the story, the students used their youthful energy to grab the audience's attention.
Rui: The best of both halves meshed together seamlessly to create something greater... That was my impression, at least.
Nene: It's like they grew with each passing second, you know? I really enjoyed watching that happen live...
Emu: ...!
Emu: Thank goodness...!
Tsukasa: Still, Emu, ever since we began training at Morinomiya, we knew that you were keeping an extremely busy schedule...
Tsukasa: But none of us thought that you were working on such a massive project.
Emu: Hehe. Sorry for not telling you guys sooner.
Emu: (Ever since the board approved our idea, my heart wouldn't stop racing... All the way up until today.)
Emu: (But...)
Audience: That was so good! I think I'm a fan of all of them now!!
Audience: Me too! I didn't know the students here were such amazing actors!
Audience: I know, right?! And they're probably gonna just keep growing from here. The tickets aren't too pricey, either, so I think I'll be back really soon.
Emu: All the guests are smiling and laughing.
Byakkomachi: Yeah.
Byakkomachi: I just received word that all tickets are projected to be sold out through the final showing.
Emu: Really?!
Byakkomachi: Yes. And after the reviews started going around...
Byakkomachi: It appears that more Suzurangumi fans are beginning to warm up to Kikyogumi.
Byakkomachi: Instead of comparing the two troupes, they're starting to see them as entirely different forms of entertainment.
Emu: ...! That's great!
Emu: Longtime fans of Morinomiya, and people who just discovered this place...
Emu: Is it safe to say we managed to make both groups happy?
Byakkomachi: I think so. But we still have a list of problems left to tackle...
Byakkomachi: Some in management are saying that people are only reacting superficially to something slightly new.
Byakkomachi: So, we have to keep doing everything possible to show that the success this show achieved can be repeated.
Emu: Hehe. You sound so excited, Suzu☆
Emu: I just happen to know the perfect spell that'll help you work even harder!
Byakkomachi: The perfect spell?
Emu: Yeah! Ready?
Emu: Won-Won-Wonderhoy!!
Byakkomachi: What did you do just now, Otori...?
Emu: This is a great way to give yourself a boost of energy and get more motivated to work harder!
Emu: I know you're probably gonna encounter lots and lots more obstacles in the future...
Emu: But I'm sure you'll do just fine, Suzu!
Byakkomachi: You really are an interesting person.
Byakkomachi: I'm looking forward to seeing what you'll dream of next, and how you'll make it come true.
Tsukasa: Emu is in charge of coming up with dreams for our troupe, after all!
Nene: Wait, why are you acting so proud?
Rui: I could ask you the same thing, Nene. You seem awfully happy for some reason.
Nene: I mean... I'm happy that my friend just got praised...
Emu: (Suzu, Tsukasa, Rui, Nene and everyone from the audience... They're all smiling.)
Emu: (I really love it when this happens...)
Emu: (Everyone's having fun and I get to see their sparkly smiles.)
Emu: (We had to overcome a lot of different hurdles to get here...)
Emu: (And I'm probably gonna get stuck again. I'll feel like giving up.)
Emu: (But...)
Emu: I want to be someone who keeps on trying.
Tsukasa: Hm? Did you say something just now, Emu?
Emu: Nope☆ Nothing!
